Samedi 14 novembre 2015


   C'est avec le drapeau européen et les valeurs humanistes de paix, de
   dignité et de respect que l'AEDE-france adresse son message au
   lendemain de la tragédie de Paris. Nous transmettons notre profond
   soutien aux familles des victimes. Nous exprimons notre indignation
   devant de telles tueries et nous nous associons aux trois jours de
   deuil national annoncés par le Président de la République française.
   Nous ne cèderons ni à la haine ni à la soumission.

   Nous remercions les collègues européens du réseau ELICIT-PLUS et
   internationaux d'ICP qui nous ont envoyé leurs témoignages de soutien
   ce matin.

   Pour exemple, le message d'Ari POKKA, président d'ICP:

   'Liberté, fraternité and égalité'

   Dear Colleagues,

   We have all been touched by the events in Paris on Friday night: French
   citizens are in our hearts and minds. These events were an attack on
   all of those things that are important to us as individuals, school
   leaders and ICP: freedom, democracy, respect for others and safety.
   These values are central to the work of ICP and as educators we must be
   ready to defend the values of an open society. Education is the key,
   and now more than ever, education is critical. We may not know the
   victims of these vivious attacks, but we send our warmest thoughts to
   our French colleagues and the families who have lost their dearest
   ones. Killing innocent people is not a political or religious act; it
   is a heinous crime. It is a crime for which there can be no apology. We
   hope that the people of France still have the courage to live as they
   have decided and carry on the values which have made our world a better
   place for all.

